topic.title: Partition Configuration

body.p: This region contains setup information for each partition. Each 1024-byte entry contains the partition status and state. Every partition entry includes the logical switch port count of this partition, the Upstream Port mode, and the PCI function instance ID for each P2P or vEP. The PCI function instance ID is used to address the P2P or vEP configuration register space in the PCI function CSR region and the partition events related registers. The following table shows the details for each partition configuration entry.

row.entry:
0 - Uninitialized (after reset)
1 - Active
2 - Fundamental Reset (PSC Notify)
3 - Fundamental Reset (PTD Notify)
4 - Fundamental Reset (CLEANUP TLP DONE)
5 - Hot Reset (PSC Notify)
6 - Hot Reset (PTD Notify)
7 - Hot Reset (CLEANUP TLP DONE)
8 - USP Second Bus Reset (PSC Notify)(RO)

0 - USP contains only one P2P Bridge
1 - USP contains one P2P Bridge and one NT EP
2 - USP contains one P2P Bridge and one Management EP
3 - USP contains only one NT EP(RO)

entry.p: Bit 0:7 - PCI function index N from 0 - 254 (RO)
Bit 15:21 - Port ID where logical port is 0 for partition's USP and 1 to n for partition's DSP (RO)
Bit 22:24 - PPU Channel ID that's associate to application type (RO)

li.p: 000b: PFF (P2P, vEP Management, and NT EP functions)

entry.p: Bit 0:7 - PCI function index N from 0 - 254 (RO),
Bit 16:31, USP P2P MSI Vector Number, (RO)
When a logical port in this partition has a port event, the corresponding bit is set. Overall takes up 2 Dwords(0x0104-0x10B), (RO)
When a partition event happens, the corresponding bit is set.
Bit 3 - Dynamic Partitioning Binding Command Finish, (RO)

note.p: The MRPC command will complete before the bind itself completes, so Bit 3 exists to indicate when the actual bind is complete

entry.p: Partition Hot Reset Event Header Register
Bit 0 - Event Status. 0 - No event; 1 - Event happened, (RW1C)
Bit 1 - Logged in Firmware Event Log Module
Bit 3 - Report to sideband or in-band management host based on Event Report Control Register.
Bit 5:12 - Number of times event has occurred since the last time this event was cleared, (RO)
Partition Hot Reset Event Data Registers
Takes up 20 bytes, in which the first 1 byte is valid, and the left bytes are reserved.
Bit 0 - Event Status. 0 - No event; 1 - Event happened, (RW1C)
Bit 1 - Logged in Firmware Event Log Module
Bit 3 - Report to sideband or in-band management host based on Event Report Control Register.
Bit 5:12 - Number of times event has occurred since the last time this event was cleared, (RO)
Takes up 20 bytes, in which the first 2 bytes are valid, and the left bytes are reserved.
Bit 0 - Event Status. 0 - No event; 1 - Event happened, (RW1C)
Bit 1 - Logged in Firmware Event Log Module
Bit 3 - Report to sideband or in-band management host based on Event Report Control Register.
Bit 5:12 - Number of times event has occurred since the last time this event was cleared, (RO)
Takes up 20 bytes, in which the first 2 bytes are valid, and the left bytes are reserved.
Dynamic Partitioning Binding Command Finish Event Header Registers
Bit 0 - Event Status. 0 - No event; 1 - Event happened, (RW1C)
Bit 1 - Logged in Firmware Event Log Module
Bit 3 - Report to sideband or in-band management host based on Event Report Control Register.
Bit 5:12 - Number of times event has occurred since the last time this event was cleared, (RO)
Dynamic Partitioning Binding Command Finish Event Data Registers
Bit 0:159, Logical port bitmask. When a bit is set, it means there is "Dynamic partitioning MRPC binding command finish" event in corresponding logical port, (RO)
Reserved for customers to implement up to 6 vendor-specific events, 24 bytes per event.
